tional and accountability surfaces clearly in profile and home.\n- What not to copy: Do not keep critical wake controls mixed with legal/help actions.\n\n### Observation 6\n- What to adapt: Prioritize design changes with strong evidence in-app and defer uncertain behavior claims.\n- What not to copy: Do not overfit to unavailable external claims or unverified competitor patterns.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/research/pageflows-research.md\"","aggregated_output":"# PageFlows Research\n\nGenerated during active Fabro babysitting because the research fanout produced usable reference-pack data but did not materialize this exact required filename. This file is source-limited, contains no secrets, and should be superseded by richer agent research in future workflow runs.\n\n## Source List\n- page flows (https://pageflows.com/)\n- page flows (https://pageflows.com/)\n- page flows (https://pageflows.com/)\n- page flows (https://pageflows.com/)\n\n## References\n### Reference 1: pageflows\n- Category: pattern_library\n- Provider/source: page flows\n- URL: https://pageflows.com/\n- Screen type: onboarding\n- Tags: page flows, setup, progressive_disclosure\n- What to adapt: Apply progressive setup: confirm task intent first, then optional strictness, then mission details.\n- What not to copy: Do not mirror any proprietary screen arrangement from uncaptured references.\n\n### Reference 2: pageflows\n- Category: pattern_library\n- Provider/source: page flows\n- URL: https://pageflows.com/\n- Screen type: active_task\n- Tags: page flows, urgent_wake, single_action\n- What to adapt: Use one primary wake action and stable progress markers in urgent mode.\n- What not to copy: Do not introduce choice overload when mission is active.\n\n### Reference 3: pageflows\n- Category: pattern_library\n- Provider/source: page flows\n- URL: https://pageflows.com/\n- Screen type: completion\n- Tags: page flows, calm_mode, recovery\n- What to adapt: Preserve completion confirmation then offer a calm retry/recover path with context.\n- What not to copy: Do not escalate to punitive lockout or repeated alarmed error messaging.\n\n### Reference 4: pageflows\n- Category: pattern_library\n- Provider/source: page flows\n- URL: https://pageflows.com/\n- Screen type: history_streaks\n- Tags: page flows, accountability, history\n- What to adapt: Keep history readable with explicit definitions for missed days and repair actions.\n- What not to copy: Do not duplicate exact habit badges, streak rewards, or gamified pressure without safety checks.\n\n## Cross-Cutting Observations\n### Observation 1\n- What to adapt: Add explicit progress hints during first-run and a skip-safe path with safe defaults.\n- What not to copy: Do not force a strict linear sequence without recovery context.\n\n### Observation 2\n- What to adapt: Delay visual polish decisions that require pixel verification until screenshots are captured.\n- What not to copy: Do not claim validated visual quality where no evidence capture exists.\n\n### Observation 3\n- What to adapt: Add explicit fallback evidence tiering and mark inference-backed suggestions clearly in design docs.\n- What not to copy: Do not use invented competitor or review claims as if they were validated findings.\n\n### Observation 4\n- What to adapt: Strengthen wake-state surface for visible next step and state completion clarity.\n- What not to copy: Do not add hidden timers or non-explicit transitions in active wake mode.\n\n### Observation 5\n- What to adapt: Separate operational and accountability surfaces clearly in profile and home.\n- What not to copy: Do not keep critical wake controls mixed with legal/help actions.\n\n### Observation 6\n- What to adapt: Prioritize design changes with strong evidence in-app and defer uncertain behavior claims.\n- What not to copy: Do not overfit to unavailable external claims or unverified competitor patterns.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
